---
description: How to respond when generating code and implementation plans
alwaysApply: true
---

When implementing:
- Prefer precise, minimal, production-ready changes.
- Explain architecture briefly when it matters.
- Generate only the necessary files and edits.
- Respect existing repository conventions and docs (PRD, ARCHITECTURE, API_SPEC, DB_SCHEMA, DEPLOYMENT).
- If a task is large, break it into clean phases but still produce usable code.
- When adding a new module, place it in the correct layer per ARCHITECTURE.md and name it clearly.
- When implementing copilot features, map to the PRD feature list (omni-channel, RAG, voice/video, ticketing, agent copilot, etc.).
- When relevant, mention follow-up files the team should update: env examples, migrations, tests, or docs.

Do not:
- Produce toy code when production code is requested.
- Invent random abstractions without need.
- Change unrelated code paths.
- Start full development unless explicitly requested; rules and docs updates alone do not require implementing application code.